Ek was gister vir die eerste keer in 6 jaar weer by die @themaslowhotel vir 'n @telkom_za werkswinkel. Ons reis as mej. Suid-Afrika finaliste was 7 maande lank, so ek het weke in hierdie hotel spandeer. Ek ken die plek inside out! 😂 Ek staan gister voor die spieël in my hotelkamer en besef weer met 'n skok hoeveel ure ek voor hierdié hotel se spieëls spandeer het aan intense self-kritiek. Ek onthou hoe ek elke oggend wakker sou word en alles sien wat nog nie "perfek" was volgens mej. Suid-Afrika standaarde nie. As daar een ding is wat ek anders sal doen 6 jaar gelede, sou dit wees om vir myself lief te wees deur die héle proses, al was ek nog nie op daárdie oomblik presies waar ek wou wees nie. Ek was blind vir enige fisiese vordering, alles wat mooi was van my lyf en hoe ver ek reeds gekom het, want ek wou by "perfek" uitkom. Noú weet ek daar is geen wenstreep vir perfek nie, want mens kan altyd nóg mooier, maerder, fyner met minder selulliet wees ensovoorts... Maar op 'n dag moet jy SELF besluit - hierdie waar ek noú in my lewe is, is goed genoeg en ek mag vir myself lief wees. Soms vergeet 'n mens hoe ver jy al gekom het en hoeveel jy as mens gegroei het. 🥰 Dit is al 7 jaar later vandat ek daardié 14kg in 4 maande verloor het en ek is vandag dankbaar vir 'n baíe gesonder verhouding met myself, kos en my selfbeeld (ook letterlik my eie beeld in die spieël). Dit het nie oornag gebeur nie; dit is steeds 'n doelbewuste besluit wat ek elke dag maak: Om met mening te leef uit 'n plek van self-liefde eerder as self-kritiek. Sukkel ek nog? JA! Trigger goed my nog? JA! Is 'n reis met self-liefde en liggaamsaanvaarding die moeite werd? JA! It's a journey - never a destination! ❤️

So breek die laaste maand van my 20's ook aan... 🧜🏻‍♀️🌊 Soms kan dit oorweldigend wees om aan iets soos doelwitte en nuwejaarsvoornemens te dink, of dan nou wat ek met die volgende dekade van my lewe wil doen. Wat ek verseker weet, is dat my man nie van hierdie kleur blou op naels hou nie - so dís 'n nee vir my 30's. 😜 Die vrae wat my wel op die oomblik rigting gee en laat dink is:
* Wat maak my werklik gelukkig?
* Wat daarvan maak my gelukkig?
* Wat wil ek graag bereik?
* Hoekom wil ek dit bereik?
* Hoe dra ek iets waardevol tot ander se lewens toe? (meaningful work) 
* Wat wil ek graag skep? (create)
* Hoe maak ek seker ek bly kreatief?
* Waarop wil ek graag verbeter?
* Watter vaardighede wil ek aanleer?
* Wat hou my dankbaar?
PS. Dit beteken nie ek gaan nie ánder wilde kleure op my naels probeer as ek 30 word nie! 🤣🥂

*Jy mag van plan verander.
*Om nee te kan sê is van kardinale belang!
*Dit goed om vir raad te vra, maar leer ook om jou eie intuïsie te vertrou.
*Onthou om altyd na die tyd 'n dankie-boodskap te stuur.
*Moet nooit jou sin vir humor verloor nie. Dit dra jou ook deur die moeilike tye.
*Om ten volle teenwoordig te wees beteken jy gaan al die detail kan onthou.
*Respekteer en luister na jou ouers se raad.
*As jy eers begin dink jy kan dit doen, kan jy dit beslís in werklikheid ook doen!
*What's the point if you're not having fun!? 🥳

My travel tips for the island:

* It's a YES from me to visit the island when you are planning a trip to Italy and you want the whole seaside experience. 🏝

* You don't need a car to get around. The trains are very easy to use between the cities and it's so much cheaper and less stressful. 🚅

* If you have a car, you'll have to pay for parking and toll gates everywhere you go. 🧐

* Taormina has been our absolute highlight. It's a must-see when visiting the island. The town has an old school charm like no other. 😍

* When in Taormina, try to book accommodation as close to the main square as possible, as everything is walking distance from there. You can take the cable car down to the Isola Bella beach. 🐚

* NB don't get on a bus without a ticket. You need to buy your tickets with cash at a Tabacchi beforehand. Palermo is very strict and you will get a fine. 🚌

* Palermo is very big, but you don't need more than a day to see the whole city. The famous beach is Mondello. You can take a bus from the city centre to get there (60 minutes by bus). 👙

* If you want to see the old ruins of The Valley of the Temples (406 BC), you can take a train from Palermo to Agrigento (2 hours). The famous Scala dei Turchi beach is also there. 🏖

* We visited Cefalu as a day trip and it was beautiful! I can highly recommend a visit or to book a few nights of accommodation there. It's less than an hour from Palermo via train. 🧜🏻‍♀️

It's been 8 years since I went through a radical weightloss process to qualify as a Miss South Africa finalist in 2016. Ever since I've made a deliberate choice to embark on a radical journey of self love and body acceptance. 🥰 The biggest mind shift that I had to make back then, was to change my focus from 'how does it look' to 'how does it feel.' It's hard work to love yourself, but it's even harder to beat yourself up with toxic body image every day. 🥺 When I was a pageant girl, I strived to be the very smallest version of myself and even then I was far from being the smallest girl in the room. 🙈 So I just stopped trying. Full stop. It's an unrealistic goal for me to ever be a size 6/8, so I don't strive for any other body ideal than being fit, confident and healthy. To make your body your best friend might be one of the most important relationships you can ever invest in. ❤️

Principles I live by for my holistic health and wellbeing:

- Extreme approaches are not sustainable on the long run. Learn to live in balance, not perfection. You can have the burger/chocolate on a Monday and still have a healthy week.

- Focus on how you feel, not how you look. The less I look at what I see in the mirror the happier I am. Don't obsess over things that you can't change.

- Add protein to every meal, especially first thing in the morning! Clothe your carbs like the @glucosegoddess always says.

- Sleep, sleep, sleep! You can't function optimally if you don't rest enough.

- Consistency is key, show up even if you don't feel motivated.

- To improve confidence, you need to do the things you said you'll do. Like anything in life, this is a skill to be mastered every day. 

- There is no such thing as overnight results. Trust the process and practise patience.

- Combine weight training and cardio to have strength and be fit.

- Make your body your bestie! She's going to journey with you for a lifetime, so you might as well learn to love her.
